    hdTitle6: "Material selection and material testing",
    mmBio: "Since there is currently no purely biological and therefore natural repair and restoration material in dentistry, oral medicine and jaw medicine, it is advisable to test materials intraorally for each patient individually using kinesiology and an arm length test). Conventional medical test methods such as skin tests (epi or intracutaneous test) are often inadequate because these can usually only detect part of the intolerance, namely the real allergy to a substance. It should be noted that each test only reflects the status on the day of the test and does not allow any statement for the future. For example, a material initially tested as compatible can later turn out to be incompatible. This is due to Remember that sensitization to a material in the sense of an allergy can occur at any time, even years later. In addition, the respective state of energy and the ability to regulate play (is tested with a decoder).",
    hdTitle7: "Ozone therapy in dentistry",
    oBio1: "The disinfecting effect of ozone is scientifically proven. Even the smallest amounts have a germicidal effect on 99 percent of all microorganisms, including viruses, bacteria and fungi. A short-term increase in blood flow is also proven. This effect is based on the fact that the vessels are briefly closed and react to this a little later by expanding.",
