    hBio2: "Homeopathic adjunctive therapy often proves its worth in dental interventions. We use homeopathic remedies before and after extractions, accompanying periodontitis (gum disease). In pediatric dentistry, children susceptible to caries are given individual homeopathic remedies depending on their genetic characteristics (constitution).",
    hdTitle9: "Ear and oral acupuncture",
    eaTitle1: "What is ear acupuncture?",
    eaBio1: "Ear acupuncture or auriculotherapy is a holistic treatment method in which the surface of the ear serves as a reflex zone for all organs of the body. This therapy offers an effective solution to pain in the head area and throughout the body. In combination with trigger point therapy, it enables effective pain relief. In addition, it also offers a vegetative compensation for stress and other complaints. Ear acupuncture or auriculotherapy is therefore a comprehensive method for promoting health and well-being.",
    eaTitle2: "What is oral acupuncture?",
    eaBio2: "Oral acupuncture is an effective treatment method that uses the phenomenon of somatotopic projection systems. With local anesthetic injections into the oral mucosa, diagnoses are made and therapies carried out as part of the neural therapeutic interference field search. This innovative approach makes it possible to localize disorders in the body and treat them in a targeted manner. The precise placement of the injections at specific points in the oral cavity effectively alleviates symptoms and promotes overall health. Oral acupuncture is therefore a promising method for improving well-being.",
