    drBio3: "All parts of the body, such as the heart, are shown in precisely localizable reflex zones on the ear, hand and foot. The dental reflex method uses the reflex zones on the foot to check the individual tooth regions for damage. In this way it can also be determined whether existing health disorders and symptoms of illness are caused by herds in the tooth and jaw area.",
    drTitle: "When is a Dental Reflex successful?",
    drBio4: "With a dental procedure, usually minimally invasive (keyhole surgery), these foci are minimized or completely removed. This can often eliminate symptoms and improve health. However, it must be said that the therapy is only successful in small herds; for larger ones, a surgical intervention with generous shaping of the focal tissue must be carried out.",
    arTitle: "Amalgam restoration",
